main event: A witness in Janesville, Wisconsin observed a blue, glowing, oval-shaped object that moved rapidly in the sky on February 5, 1965.
interesting points: The object had a long, triangular tail with a flashing blue light.
The object made a high-pitched whining sound and moved back and forth across the horizon.
Multiple witnesses in the area reported seeing similar objects on other occasions.
The object was described as being about 300 feet away and 1,000 feet high, and it illuminated the dark sky.
The witness called a local radio station to report the sighting.
sighted object: a large, oval-shaped object with a blue glow and flashing lights
witnesses: multiple witnesses, including the primary witness who filed the report
photographs: no photographs present in the report
